xt-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Vector DNA<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Insert DNA<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Ligase Buffer (<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\/<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> reaction for 10X buffer, and <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\/<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> reaction for 5X buffer)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">-<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> T4 DNA Ligase<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">H<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>O to a total of <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"E20DBFC02C2711EAB7E47FC1CFFE8347","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":100,"unit":"ng","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"E8F9E7A02C2711EAB7E47FC1CFFE8347","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":1,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"ECA4A0202C2711EAB7E47FC1CFFE8347","order_id":4,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":10,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"EFE796202C2711EAB7E47FC1CFFE8347","order_id":5,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":2,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"F2E5BAF02C2711EAB7E47FC1CFFE8347","order_id":6,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":10,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054730,"guid":"0B621810CE7E11E9B2ABAFCD5872C9CA","order_id":7,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":0.5,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054731,"guid":"0F273660CE7E11E9B2ABAFCD5872C9CA","order_id":8,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":1,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054732,"guid":"112920E0CE7E11E9B2ABAFCD5872C9CA","order_id":9,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":10,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054733,"guid":"49E4D9FA48AF4EAA891199DBD38D288D","order_id":10,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Notes: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>If the DNA concentrations are low such that you cannot get all <\/span><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span> of DNA, buffer and ligase into a <\/span><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span> reaction, scale the reaction size as necessary - being sure to increase the amount of buffer proportionally. <\/span><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span> of ligase should be sufficient for larger ligation reactions.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>Because ligase buffer contains ATP, which degrades upon freeze\/thaw cycles, it is a good idea to take a fresh tube, thaw it one time and aliquot individual tubes of <\/span><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span>, <\/span><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span> or <\/span><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span> for storage at <\/span><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span>. Whenever you need to set up ligations in the future you can thaw a new tube that you know has only been thawed once before.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Always do controls. See the tips and general guidelines section for details<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;lis